Rectangular Prism

   Given: One vertex (top left front), height, width, depth
   Defining points: vertices
   Generate:
      x   x+w
      y   y-h
      z   z-d

Sphere

   Given: center, radius
   Defining points: points on the surface of the sphere
   Generate: make circle, rotate it around x or y axis

   x=rcos(theta) + cx
   y=rsin(theta)cos(phi) + cy
   z=rsin(theta)sin(phi) + cz
   theta: 0 -> pi
   phi: 0 -> 2*pi
   
Torus

   Given: center, circle radius, torus radius
   Defining Points: points on surface of torus
   Generate: make circle torus radius away from center, rotate around center of torus

   x= cos(phi)(rcos(theta)+R) + cx
   y= rsin(theta) + cy
   z= -sin(phi)(rcos(theta)+R) + cz
   theta: 0 -> 2*pi
   phi: 0 -> 2*pi
   
